						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab lying in Survey No. 24 near the temple of Kāśīviśvēśvara at old Kaḍṇi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṅghaṇa—A.D. 1221.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Vishu, Pushya, s11u. Pūrṇimā, Thursday,</hi> regularly corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1221, December 30, Thursday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription seems to record a gift of land made by a certain Kaḍa[ṇa] [Vā]sitara Nāgadēva.</p>						

						</summary>
